On Linux
========

* install the following packages through your package manager (following guide
  written for apt-get, tested on Ubuntu 14.10):
  - build-essential
  - libblas-dev
  - liblapack-dev
  - gfortran
  - python3
  - python3-dev
  - python3-pyqt4
  - python3-pip
  - virtualenv

* create a virtual environment:
  $ pip3 install virtualenv
  $ cd /path/to/orange3
  $ virtualenv venv_orange3 --python=python3 --system-site-packages

* activate virtual environment:
  $ source venv_orange3/bin/activate

* install requirements
  $ pip install numpy
  $ pip install -r orange3/requirements.txt
  $ python setup.py develop

* clone CPE & install its dependencies into orange3 venv:
  $ git clone https://github.com/qusp/cpe
  $ git checkout your-branch (could be develop, master, or a tag/release)
  $ pip install -r cpe/requirements.txt

* auto-generate widgets for CPE nodes:
  $ python scripts/regenerate_widgets.py --neuropype-path /your/path/to/cpe
  (you can re-invoke this command whenever you have edited your CPE code)

* for a good development experience, we recommend
  that you install and set up PyCharm:
  * open the orange3 folder from PyCharm
  * under Settings / Project: orange3 / Project Interpreter / Project Interpreter
    click the gear icon
  * click Add local..., and select the python executable in your orange3_venv/bin
    folder.
  * accept and close the settings dialog.
  * click Open, select the cpe directory and accept, and select
    "open in current window" and "add to current project".
  * in the Project pane to the left, navigate to Orange/canvas/__main__.py
  * wait until PyCharm is done parsing your packages (see
    progress bar at bottom)
  * right-click and select "Create '__main__'".
  * in the window that just opened, change the name to VPE, and under
    Script parameters, add: --clear-widget-settings
  * Now you can select VPE in the pull-down menu on the top left and either
    click the play button for a normal run or the bug button for a debug run.
  * to regenerate widgets in the VPE after a CPE code change, just right-click
    the file orange3/scripts/regenerate_widgets.py,
    and choose Run 'regenerate_widgets'
